<p>When we want to publish some DLL files as a package onto nuget.org, it is required to create a nupack file then publish it.</p><p>I was using NuGet Packager (it creates a project, add dll files into libs folder, update nuspec files, build the project in release mode, then a package will be published on nuget.org). But it is not being maintained and seems being outdate on new nuget version.</p><p>Below are simple steps to build/publish a package:</p><p>1/ Create a Package.nuspec file</p><p>Below is a sample (replace id, version, title, owners, dependencies... by yours).</p><p>Then besure that all files are added into folders libs / content / tools.</p><blockquote>&lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;<br>&lt;package &gt;<br>&nbsp; &lt;metadata&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;id&gt;Rabbit.Web.MvcNotification&lt;/id&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;version&gt;1.2.0&lt;/version&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;title&gt;Rabbit.Web.MvcNotification&lt;/title&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;authors&gt;juniho&lt;/authors&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;owners&gt;RabbitSoftware&lt;/owners&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;description&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Provides an option to display user messages<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;/description&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;releaseNotes&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;/releaseNotes&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;summary&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;/summary&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;language&gt;en-US&lt;/language&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;projectUrl&gt;https://nuget.org/packages/NuGet.Rabbit.Web.MvcNotification&lt;/projectUrl&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;iconUrl&gt;https://nuget.org/Content/Images/packageDefaultIcon-50x50.png&lt;/iconUrl&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;requireLicenseAcceptance&gt;false&lt;/requireLicenseAcceptance&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;licenseUrl&gt;http://opensource.org/licenses/Apache-2.0&lt;/licenseUrl&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;copyright&gt;Copyright @ RabbitSoftware 2018&lt;/copyright&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;dependencies&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;group targetFramework="net46"&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;dependency id="Microsoft.AspNet.Mvc" version="5.2.6" /&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;/group&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;/dependencies&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;references&gt;&lt;/references&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;tags&gt;&lt;/tags&gt;<br>&nbsp; &lt;/metadata&gt;<br>&nbsp; &lt;files&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;file src="lib\" target="lib" /&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;file src="tools\" target="tools" /&gt;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;file src="content\" target="content" /&gt;<br>&nbsp; &lt;/files&gt;<br>&lt;/package&gt;</blockquote><p>2/ Create a package with nuget pack</p><p>The command to use is</p><blockquote>nuget pack &lt;Path To Package NuSpec File&gt;</blockquote><p>3/ Publish the package to nuget.org</p><p>The command below will do the job</p><blockquote>nuget push &lt;Path To nupkg File&gt;&nbsp;-Source <a href="https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json">https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json</a></blockquote><p><b>References:</b><br></p><ul><li><a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/nuget/create-packages/publish-a-package" target="_blank">Publishing packages</a><br></li></ul>